10/11/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Representatives of the defence ministry and NATO meet on Wednesday (10 November) in Skopje to discuss the modernisation of the Krivolak military training field.
Macedonian officials say Washington has signaled readiness to support a project aimed at upgrading Krivolak, which could become a regional staff-training centre for peacekeeping operations.
In other news Tuesday, Ohrid hosted a regional conference on fighting organised crime.
Police and judicial authorities from Southeast European countries attended, as well as representatives of the Council of Europe.
(Dnevnik - 10/11/04;
A1 TV - 09/11/04)
